rComments: Il se base sur un livre obligatoire duquel proviennent toutes les lectures hebdomadaires. En plus des examens (choix de réponses et dissertation), il fait des tests surprises  à livre ouvert  tout au long de la session pour forcer la présence en classe. Aussi, il aime faire de lhumour durant ses cours et cherche à interagir avec les étudiants.
teacherRatingTags: ['Hilarious', 'Beware of pop quizzes', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: excellent prof! très clair et il explique bien. les exigences pour les exams ne sont pas une surprise et il nous prépare bien.

Overall great laidback prof: material covered is interesting and entertaining: you gotta be in class, but it's a fairly easy class, so besides doing the reading, there is very little work. Midterm and Final correspond to the material.

Very good prof, he's clearly passionate by what he's doing, gives great examples. The 1st midterm is a multiple choice exam, while the final is a 4 questions,you need to write about 1 full page for each. He also makes a quizz in the middle of every lecture, and you can use your book, so its really easy. Class is very easy to pass if you like socio
He's demanding but explain really good and give a lot of examples.

Très bon professeur. Son savoir s'étend au-delà de son champ d'expertise ce qui fait de lui le professeur parfait pour initier à la sociologie. Il n'est pas trop rapide, ce qui permet de bien comprendre le contenu, surtout dans le cadre d'un cours d'introduction. Le cours est bien structuré et cohérent, parfait pour entamer un parcours en socio.

Un super bon prof qui connait bien sa matière et est très passionné à propos des sujets qu'il enseigne. Cependant, les cours peuvent être très lent (j'ai pris deux cours de 7 à 10 et il ne donne pas de pause mais termine 20 minutes plus tôt), mais ils sont nécessaires pour bien comprendre la matière.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Lecture heavy', 'Graded by few things']

rComments: There is a quiz every class so attendance is mandatory. He embarrassed me in front of 200 students, and will call you out for being on your phone. Very monotone and takes 15 minutes to go over one slide of the powerpoint. Powerpoints are not posted on bright space. the end.

Very monotone lecture, midterm and final were heavily focused on readings found in his course pack. Readings and course material did not align well, making studying for the midterm quite difficult. The final was laid out decently  4 development questions. Overly a very boring class, however if you do your readings and participate youll be fine!
teacherRatingTags: ['Lecture heavy', 'Get ready to read', 'Clear grading criteria']

rComments: He is a good teacher, he is clear about what he wants and gives you what you need to know to succeed. The exams are based on exactly what was in the lectures and book. Had a few quizzes that are fairly easy and note boosters. I would advise you to take him he is a prettt good and chill teacher.
Very good, understanble and flexible teacher. Be in class for the quiz (although they are pretty easy, open book and you're allowed to be in groups for them.)

He teaches us stuff we have known for our entire school life and he doesn't get to the point. I would highly recommend to avoid at all cost. He is not a good teacher. But if you want a Netflix class or a class to catch up on homework hes your guy.
teacherRatingTags: ['Beware of pop quizzes', 'Get ready to read', 'Group projects']

rComments: Dr. Capitaine is a good lecturer and makes the course interesting. His midterm and exam are mostly multiple choice and he provides us with great T.A.s for the quizzes and research paper. His exams reflect his lectures very well. He does make students work to obtain a good grade but he is fair.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Gives good feedback', 'Accessible outside class']

rComments: Brieg conveys material in class well, referencing the readings and provides insight. His lectures are somewhat boring, but he elaborates well on the material. His exams are structured 80% on a development question, 20% on multiple choice. Make sure to ask for clarity on assignments!
Kinda hard to understand him & makes useless jokes that are no relevant to the class. I had a hard time following.

I took this class as in elective WORST IDEA EVER. The cours is super boring and SUPER HARD. His mid-terms might be 15% but 80% of your grade is based on 1 question that you need to develop and the remaining is based on 20 multiple question. 40% of your final grade is based on a project that makes no sense. To be safe dont take any of his classes.

Excellent professeur! Il aide beaucoup les étudiants, ses conseils sont très précieux, je l'ai eu pour deux cours, où j'ai eu de très bonnes notes avec lui.. Il donne l'occasion aux élèves de lui présenter une fois leur travail avant de le rendre définitivement, corrigé suite aux conseils du prof.

Cool class. 1 midterm, 1 project, and one final exam. Midterm and exam are multiple choices and the project is a month long. The project is usually a case study and the test/exam reflect exactly what we learn in class. Always there to help but was sometimes confusing during lectures. Either way, lectures were important.

Bon enseignant, explique bien et nous fait comprendre la matièere plus facilement. Encourage la discussion. Examens faciles èa passer, il faut une bonne étude pour avoir une trèes haute note par contre.
this teacher is good at explaining and making material easier to understand. He gets lost sometimes but overall good teacher ad easy class
